President Biden has declared a major disaster in Hawaii due to severe storms, flooding, and landslides that occurred from March 8 to March 18, 2021. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Colby Stanton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.